{"v":1,"id":"still-got-5-on-it","title":"Still Got 5 On It","duration":248.2,"envHz":12.5,"identity":{"bpm":92,"bpmExact":92.29,"key":"A#","mode":"minor","keyConf":0.67,"genre":"Hip Hop","subGenres":["Boom Bap","90s Hip Hop","R&B"],"mood":"nostalgic, gritty, noir, melancholic","energy":"medium","language":"English","vocalStyle":"raspy male lead with raw confessional tone alternating with gruff call-and-response ad-libs, contrasted by a smooth smoky R&B chorus featuring passionate vibrato and layered harmonies","styleSentence":"A grimy East Coast boom bap track at 92 BPM featuring dusty drums with heavy swing and hard snare cracks over thick vinyl hiss, anchored by a foghorn sub-bass and sinister minor-key piano; the production lifts with a bright xylophone melody doubled on mellow flute that weaves through the hook to answer raw confessional vocals from a raspy male lead rapper supported by gruff call-and-response ad-libs, while a smooth smoky R&B chorus delivers passionate vibrato in layered harmonies against muted trumpet shadows and eerie glassy synth motifs.","summary":"The song is a gritty reflection on how inflation and changing markets have devalued money ('five') while destroying the community bonds and quality found in 'the good old days' of unbranded, shared experiences. It captures a melancholic nostalgia for an era where value was defined by trust and camaraderie rather than corporate branding or rising prices.","themes":["Economic Devaluation","Lost Community Trust","Chemical Nostalgia vs. Modern Pollution","Urban Decay","Shared Struggle"],"keywords":[{"word":"five","emotion":"Loss of value/trust","imageryPrompt":"A small crumpled dollar bill floating in a void, its edges burning away into gray ash."},{"word":"mystery","emotion":"Dread/uncertainty","imageryPrompt":"Thick fog rolling off dark water where shadowy figures stand motionless under flickering sodium lights."},{"word":"candy","emotion":"Disgust/fake sweetness","imageryPrompt":"Bright artificial colors oozing from a cracked pipe, contrasting sharply with the dull grime around it."},{"word":"brand","emotion":"Alienation/indifference","imageryPrompt":"A giant corporate logo stamped over a faceless crowd of people walking in unison like robots."},{"word":"trust","emotion":"Heartbreak/betrayal","imageryPrompt":"Two hands reaching out to shake but fading into smoke before they make contact, leaving only empty air."},{"word":"chemical","emotion":"Illness/fear","imageryPrompt":"Viscous purple liquid dripping from a ceiling onto a rusty floor, bubbling with unnatural light."}]},"tone":{"brightness":2976.7,"dynamicsDb":13.1},"palette":["#080808","#181818","#282828","#383838","#484848"],"boundaries":[15.51,170.9,184.74,190.12,192.45,210.65,212.79,244.27],"sections":[{"name":"Intro","start":6.14,"end":39.7,"intensity":0.06,"emotion":"Confused longing and weary resignation as the narrator questions where value has gone.","colorHint":"#1a0f0f"},{"name":"Verse 1","start":39.7,"end":113.56,"intensity":0.76,"emotion":"Raw storytelling and bittersweet memory, contrasting past unity with current isolation.","colorHint":"#2c241b"},{"name":"Chorus","start":113.56,"end":148.83,"intensity":0.76,"emotion":"Aggressive lamentation, repeating the core truth that money no longer holds its spiritual or communal weight.","colorHint":"#4e3d2b"},{"name":"Bridge","start":148.83,"end":186.94,"intensity":0.7,"emotion":"Urgent plea for return to shared values and simple, honest connection.","colorHint":"#4a3b28"},{"name":"Drop","start":186.94,"end":192.22,"intensity":0.52,"emotion":"Defeated acceptance and cynical dismissal of repeated attempts to fix what is broken.","colorHint":"#2c1b18"},{"name":"Verse 2","start":192.22,"end":248.2,"intensity":0.84,"emotion":"Resigned observation of value eroding over time, accepting that 'five' is now dead.","colorHint":"#1a1816"}],"stems":[{"name":"drums","family":"rhythm","peak":99,"active":99,"env":[0,0,62,65,56,51,45,7,3,4,58,60,47,3,51,51,18,6,44,4